# Picking the load balancer

## ALB — Layer 7 (HTTP)

Terminates + parses HTTP, routes on **content**. Model: **listener → rules → target group**. Targets: `instance` · `ip` · `lambda`. Default for **web apps, APIs, microservices**.

## NLB — Layer 4 (TCP/UDP)

Moves packets — fast, protocol-agnostic. **Static IP per AZ**, **preserves source IP**, millions req/s, **only LB with UDP**. For IP whitelisting, non-HTTP, low latency.

## GWLB — Layer 3 (niche)

Transparent inline bump for **third-party firewalls / IDS**, via **GENEVE :6081**. "Deploy appliances scalably + transparently."
